caption: This local spot is one of those "exactly what you expect" neighborhood places where they know you, take care of you, and serve good food and friendly atmosphere. There's nothing fancy but there's always something comforting about chatting with your favorite staff. Moreover, they have been proactive and intentional about making safe space during the pandemic. That alone deserves neighborhood loyalty!
Love this place.

Went twice with my partner and we really enjoyed all the food. I asked for a few changes in the dishes we ordered and the crew was flexible with all requests. Food is truly amazing, we loved the place. We tried different things and they were all wonderful. The waiters are also very careful about covid. Totally recommend this place!
The best Mexican food in DC, amazing tacos, chimichanga and enchiladas. The guacamole is delicious. The staff are awesome

What an awesome place! Been ordering dinner for the family from here for a while. We decided to have them cater a small party and they knocked it out of the park. The chicken saltado is awesome. Can't wait to go back.
(Translated by Google) Delicious food ..  (Original) Deliciosa la comida..

True Tex-Mex vibes!  The tortilla soup tastes like there’s an abulela cooking in the back.  Spicy mango margarita was delish...  warm hospitality.  Gracias por todos Cesar!  Next trip will be for a nice brunch, take me back to my San Antonio, TX days.  Oh, and they bring chips & salsa to the table, classic!
Not LGBT+ Friendly. Very rude comments made about my table when they thought we couldn’t understand them.
Very tasty Tex-Mex food this Is a very pleasant restaurant the serves are attentive overall awesome customer service! I would highly recommend this restaurant.
First time here and SO impressed. Veggie fajitas had so many different veggies and I loved the black beans. We will be back SOON!!! Absolutely amazing food and service.

Very unfriendly. Customer service leaves much to be desired. The older man who works there did not greet me when I entered. When I asked to order a hibiscus margarita, he inspected my driver’s license very suspiciously as if it were fake. Then, I went to sit outside and since the patio was empty, I sat at a four-chair table in the sun. He hastily came outside and asked me to move to a smaller, two-person table. I was going to invite my friends who live around the corner to drink with me, but after that, I changed my mind quickly. I will NOT be back. Que pena.

(Translated by Google) The food has nothing to do with the Mexican, the ugly beans, the nachos not well cooked, and not to mention the rice with the meat, I didn't like how expensive it was to go to dinner.  (Original) La comida no tiene nada que ver con lo mexicano los frijoles feos los nachos no bien cocinados y no se diga el arroz con la carne no me gusto más lo caro que me salio ir a cenar
I gotta start with saying the guacamole is WAYYYYYY too oniony. The staff is very nice, have wonderful manners and are attentive to the customers. The esquires was unclear on what it was but ¯_(ツ)_/¯

If you like a considerable amount of booze in your margaritas then please stop by and try the Frozen Habanero-Mango Margarita as well as the Homemade Traditional Margarita ....no not out of a damn bottle like some places around the area that I won't name. This is definitely one of the best that will stay on my list of best places to come back to again and again.😁 #margaritaville #thetop10 #awesome #thankyou #spicy #elcamino #dc

The food here is absolutely amazing, a taste of authentic Mexican style cuisine including a spectacular and friendly service. My favorite of all was the mango habiscus frozen margarita, it was soooo good! We will totally come back to visit since we are from NYC!

THIS restaurant was shut, with staff inside mind you, at 12:12 when the hours read 1am. I would say this needs to be rectified. Prior to that their phone number was called, perhaps a half hour earlier to no avail. This is my review. Some of the tacos in the picture looked good. I wish I was so fortunate to know, for a fact.
The food is fantastic. Ceviche unbelievable. Tacos a must have.

(Translated by Google) The food is very good, the cocktails are well prepared and the attention is very good.  (Original) La comida muy buena los cocteles bien preparados y la atencion super bien se los recomiendo
One of my favorite restaurants in D.C. If you are looking for amazing margaritas, salsa, and or carne asada this is the spot.
Very friendly and attentive staff. The patio is lovely. The margaritas are amazing! The tacos and the nachos left something to be desired, but on the whole it was a great experience!

This place is the worst . I ordered door dash and the rice wasn’t even in the box it was all over the bag. The steak was so undercooked I threw it away. Literally it was red and raw . They put one piece of broccoli. The disappointment of this place is unbelievable. Never ordering from here again.
We ordered from here via third party app and the food was excellent! The flautas were incredible! Would definitely recommend. The food came before the delivery window as well.
I'm very happy with the new management - the menu simplified and improved in authenticity, and the kitchen does a wonderful job. I highly recommend their traditional dishes.

Cute authentic Mexican eatery, ample bar space. Small seating area in the back with a few tables up front. Margaritas are excelent,  passionfruit margarita, the punch margarita and the classic are a group fav. Nachos aren't anything to write home about. The tacos are excellent. The food can be a little spicey to some pallets but overall an amazing spot.to grab food and drinks.
(Translated by Google) Recommend the melted queso  (Original) Recommend the queso fondu
We had carne asada and tacos al pastor. Fresh and flavorful!
We stumbled upon this place while visiting D.C. and it was so perfect! Food was amazing and service was wonderful
Whole Sea Bass was nothing less than amazing. I believe it's the chef special. Definitely coming back when it's warmer so I can enjoy the outdoor eating area.
Amazing fajita. Fresh ingredients. Fast service. Big fan.
Great bar. Great service

I loved this place! Authentic food with very nice servers, like Jacki. Complementary tortilla chips and salsa served before the meal. Not many options for their Jarrito drinks. Excellent quesadillas and tres leches.

I love this place. I’ve been for brunch a couple times now since it’s reopened and it’s amazing - food is great (the beans are DELICIOUS), service is super friendly, prices are pretty cheap. Bottomless mimosas are only $14 to add and not everyone at the table has to do it which is great. Best Bloody Mary I’ve ever had in DC! I always leave feeling like I should come here more often. They have happy hour all day Sunday and Monday! Definitely want to return for dinner sometime, it has a great friendly neighborhood restaurant vibe.
Super underrated place!! William (bartender) was incredibly attentive, helpful, and efficient. Food flavor doesn't hold back, and prices are fair.
Love the newest menu!
Great local spot for Mexican food. Usually it's not too busy.
Great! Perfect!
The food was delicious and the drinks and the bartenders great and personable!
I went on a Monday evening. The service was great.
Great place. Good drinks great food and a wonderful bartender William.

This place is an unexpected treat.....and that statement is from a Texan. The quesadilla plate was well presented and delicious. The carne con huevos (that’s a ny strip steak, cooked to order and topped with eggs) was tremendous. Great food all round. Marvin is a joy to speak with and has been told he is welcome to come to Texas and feed us forever.

New Owners! New menu! Made to order guacamole.  Fresh ceviche and perfect chicken flautas. Bartenters Angel and William are very personable and skilled.The special seafood soup is out of this world! It should be a staple on the menu......phenomenal!

Great service! I visited when it  first opened under different ownership and this experience was much better. The food and drinks were delicious, especially the plantains, pork entree, and mezcal cocktail. Good portions too. Will definitely be coming back.
Good happy hour 5-7. Great food.

Amazing service from Angel and Ashley! They brought an extra basket of complimentary chips for only 3 people. The guac was made fresh and is every time. And the Sol beer with the lime wedge is so refreshing. An iconic staple to the greater Washington D.C. area.  UPDATE: My new FAVORITE place. I came back and somehow service was even BETTER than 10/10. The happy hour was extended and the bartender was responsive. Don't go anywhere else, this is your next stop.

Just reopened under new ownership.  I ate amazing carne asada and their margaritas are made with fresh ingredients.  Fresh veggies, rice & beans too.   Still have some website issues to resolve but this place is back and better than ever!

I was happy to hear el Camino has reopened but the new menu is disappointing. The vegetarian options were almost non-existent compared to before and the homemade salsas from before are no longer. The one salsa they had was mediocre and the tacos were average at best. I’ll take another chance at trying out their cocktails but don’t see much hope.
LOCATION IS CLOSED.
Loved this place for lunch and brunch. Sad to see it close
Great artwork on the walls and atmosphere.  Good food, had two tacos and sides, all were tasty. Very nice and friendly staff with quick service from the kitchen.

Honestly shocked seeing all the bad reviews - I live in the neighborhood and eat/happy hour at el Camino regularly! Their brunch is fantastic and their margaritas are delicious, I would recommend this restaurant to anyone!

It's just plain dirty. The tables are sticky, the menus are filthy, the floor has food on it. There is a reason it's dark. Been there three times. Food was decent, but over priced the first visit. The second visit is when I noticed the sticky tables. I was feeling ambivalent, but stayed. Ended up walking out after waiting 10 minutes for a server - it was not busy.  Today, the table was sticky again and the menu covered in crud. The staff was rude when I brought it up. Never going back. Can only imagine what the kitchen looks like.
Delicious and Authentic

Worst meal I've ever had.  Margaritas tasted like salty water, the enchiladas were near inedible, and wine was watered down grape juice.  Even the chips and salsa were bad.  We just wanted to get out of there but took over 30 minutes to get the check.

The food is great but the service is really really bad even when they are not busy.  Staff fighting in front of customers, leaving the bar unattended to go fight in the back, really bad because I have enjoyed this place in the past.  Went in last night on a Saturday night and they were busy but I waited 10 min for a simple hello and glass of water which never came.  I gave them a second chance today and this is my review.  Great food, bad service.

Do not eat here.  I call to order food and they were so rude because I asked how I can customize from Ubereats and the woman responded “I don’t know,” yelling and screaming at me.   I was super nice and polite. Then slammed the phone.  Then I call back to speak to a manager and the same employee says the manager is too busy, tells me I can shove it and slams the phone again.  All I was was trying to order food for my child.  Shame on them for the rudeness.  They don’t know customer service.

Average Mexican food with a nice outdoor space. The food, service, and ambiance are all fine, but nothing to rave about. However, in the long stretch of Rhode Island between Shaw and the Rhode Island Metro station, this is your one stop for your Mexican craving, so enjoy.

This is literally one of those “charge more money cause we can bc we’re in DC ‘restaraunts’ . NO you can’t. This place sucks food and service was pretty bad. Idc how close to my home your are I won’t come here again.  Stale chips , replaced with stale chips, literally having to battle the bartenders attention with other staff. How about take care of the customer? This place isn’t here for the right reasons, just another over priced place taking advantage of had working individual.  -management : check the cams - my body language says it all
Little hole in the wall place.had very good food and service.  Also had cool art.
Solid neighborhood Mexican joint. It might not blow you away, but it won't leave you disappointed either. Reasonably priced by DC standards.

Considering the reviews; I was looking forward to some awesome food. There was a huge disparity between the excellent quality of the service and the tacos served - they were a bit lifeless and unappealing on the plate. There’s a few artworks decorating the walls which are also for sale which I thought was a call element to the place
Go see Chrissy she is the best bartender in the city!
Come here for the late night happy hour! Great neighborhood vibe.

I passed this place all the time and finally had the opportunity to eat here, we came for brunch. It's very small and displays local artists work and sells it which was cool. The food was not bad, we ordered the salsa & chips and guac for appetizers, they were good but we paid $10 for a small amount of guac. Then we ordered the Mexican breakfast torta which was good, the omelets which was also good, the chocolate chip cornmeal pancakes I didn't like them at all but the others did and, the French toast because it had orange juice marinated bananas, but they didn't come with it and when we asked the server they didn't know that it came with them and then came back to tell us they ran out. It bothered us a lot that we had to inquire and that they didn't notify us and honestly the French toast looked pretty pathetic and the cherries they were talking about were marichino not real cherries lol. Overall it was good but not great.

Came for dessert which they said was “chocolate flan”. It was not flan, it was regular chocolate cake with a bunch of strange toppings like a puddle of heavy cream, cherries and sprinkles. I wanted to try this place for a good while but it was disappointing. Service was mediocre.
(Translated by Google) Very clean polite staff  (Original) Muy limpio personal educado
My favorite place to eat in the area!
Nice cocktails but at an inappropriate price for the atmosphere
Great food. Reasonably priced. Relaxed atmosphere.
(Translated by Google) I bought takeout and I had to throw it away The worst tacos you can imagine  (Original) Compre comida para llevar y la tuve que tirar Los peores tacos que te puedas imaginar
Awesome Mexican for great value on the dollar.
Food was awesome and the margs were great during happy hour.
Great atmosphere but the food was less than stellar.  Maybe it was just what my guest and I had...
Aggressively mediocre

The waitress (Brianna) was extremely rude,lazy, and disrespectful (and by disrespectful I mean she rolled her eyes as my grandmother was trying to order)!!The service was extremely slow, after 20 min. of waiting she finnaly brought our drinks, rudely put them on the table and walked away without asking if we were ready to order.
Fish tacos are spicy and good.  5-7 happy hour $1 chips and salsa are awesome.  Refried beans are not your normal looking beans, but are very good.
THIS IS NOT A ONE $ MEAL, YOU HAVE TO PAY FOR CHIPS AND SALSA, DO NOT GO HERE IF YOU ARE LOOKING FOR A ONE $ MEAL. the atmosphere was pretty cool though not gonna lie
Blown away by the food at this spot and they make a mean mixed drink as well
Great neighborhood bar. Tacos are great and you cannot beat $1 salsa and chips during happy hour!
Great food and prices...service can be a bit slow

Late night tacos and burritos every night after the normal kitchen menu ends. Sunday-Thursday 10:30pm to 11:30pm. Friday & Saturday 11:30pm - 12:30am.  Also Happy Hours Monday-Friday 5-7pm & 10:30pm - close with $3 Tecate tall boys, $5 Margaritas, $5 Negra Modelo drafts, $5 red or white wine, $5 rail drinks & $1 chips and salsa!
Outstanding people work here. Excellent and friendly service. Great organization!
Kind service. Great food and modern twist on Mexican favorites. Drink menu is great as well. We go to El Camino all the time.
Brunch was great. Service was quite slow, but I wasn't lookibg for a hasty meal, and the food was tremendous.
The service was great and excellent Happy hour.
I love the happy hour. Friendly neighborhood bar with good drinks and tacos
Good food, good experience. Ryan is one of the mangers. He's awesome. He came to clear out table and asked if I liked the special. I come here and lot and I've never had a bad experience!
Great food. Great cocktails. Great fun. If you like any of the above, don't think twice, it's nice for the price.
I ordered the vegetarian burrito and it came with meat in it. When I realized that I tried to call them it was already closed.
Great food, amazing bartender, and drinks. First time in DC, great place to go.
Jon was amazing
Fresh, innovative Mexican cuisine. Tacos are outstanding. Black bean soup hits the spot. Mains are decent. Service is friendly.
Quaint neighborhood spot with above average Mexican fare.  We had some tacos, black bean soup and chips & guac.  Service was good.  Worth a trip back explore more of the menu.
Great food, great staff. Lively atmosphere and their cocktails are superb!
Delicious! Lots of inventive Mexican food, not your run of the mill menu items. Best and most overlooked brunch in Bloomingdale/Shaw.
(Translated by Google) It is very nice place, with very good food and above all excellent service  (Original) Es in lugar muy agradable, con muy buena comida y sobre todo exelente servicio
It's ok. With all the good ratings I thought it would be better. My girlfriend and I thought the food was meh.  I don't feel like they served anything I couldn't make just as well
Great brunch
Brunch was awesome- loved the chilaquiles!  And cucumber margarita is the best.
Fantastic tacos, the chilaquiles was killer, and the vibe is awesome.
Their tacos are wonderful! The guac is great! The house cocktails are fresh and tasty. Limited table space, but a great addition to the neighborhood.

I'm excited to have this new edition to the neighborhood. That said, I was underwhelmed with the food. The Tostada was delicious for an appetizer. However, the beef short rib was way not prepared well and was flavorless. I'll head back to try again though.
Best tacos in town (especially the chicken tacos). But I'm biased.
